  "intent_precise": "Swift Rapid NGS Part 1 - Reverse Transcription: Using samp_plate (pcr_plate, slot 2), alum_tuberack (labware, slot 4), mag_plate (pcr_plate, slot 6), reservoir (reservoir, slot 2). With thermocycler module, temperature module, magnetic module. (1) Pause: Replace empty tip racks (2) Open thermocycler lid. (3) Operate thermocycler. (4) Set temperature to 25\u00b0C. (5) Set temperature to 4\u00b0C. (6) Transfer from source (A1, A1) to destination (A1, A1). (7) Pause: Mastermix solution made. Mix thouroughly and pulse spin -\n                 after, place tube rack back on the temperature module for\n                 mastermix to be distributed. (8) Transfer from source to destination. (9) Mix 15 times at 20\u00b5L. (10) Pause: Mastermix distributed and mixed thouroughly -\n                 pulse spin to collect contents. Seal plate and place back\n                 on deck. After, the thermocycler lid\n                 will automatically close and begin the heating and cooling\n                 steps.  If needed, please empty trash. (11) Close thermocycler lid. (12) Run thermocycler profile for 1 cycles. (13) Set temperature to 4\u00b0C. (14) Open thermocycler lid. (15) Pause: Move sample plate from Thermocycler to Magnetic Module (16) Mix 15 times at 80\u00b5L. (17) Incubate for 8 minutes. (18) Pause: Remove magnetic plate from deck, seal and spin down -\n                 place back on the magnetic module.\n                 If needed, please empty trash. (19) Engage magnets for bead separation. (20) Incubate for 5 minutes. (21) Transfer 100\u00b5L from source to destination. (22) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (23) Wait 30 seconds. (24) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (25) Disengage magnets to release beads. (26) Pause: Seal and spin down sample plate -\n                if needed, please empty trash. (27) Pause for incubation. (28) Transfer 12\u00b5L from source to destination. (29) Mix 10 times at 20\u00b5L. (30) Incubate for 4 minutes. (31) Disengage magnets to release beads. (32) Pause: Seal and spin down sample plate -\n             remove seal, then place back on magnet.\n             If needed, please empty trash. (33) Engage magnets for bead separation. (34) Incubate for 3 minutes. (35) Transfer 12\u00b5L from source to destination.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (4\u00b0C, 25\u00b0C), thermocycling. (volumes 12\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~22 min total)",
  "intent": "For the Swift Rapid NGS Part 1 Reverse Transcription protocol, you'll need to set up your deck with the sample plate in slot 2, aluminum tube rack in slot 4, and magnetic plate in slot 6, along with your thermocycler, temperature, and magnetic modules. Start by replacing empty tip racks, then prepare the thermocycler at 25\u00b0C and cool the temperature module to 4\u00b0C before transferring mastermix from A1 to A1 and mixing 15 times at 20\u00b5L - make sure to pulse spin and seal the plate before running the thermocycler profile for 1 cycle. Once complete, move the sample plate to the magnetic module, mix 15 times at 80\u00b5L, incubate for 8 minutes, then engage magnets for 5 minutes before performing the wash transfers (100\u00b5L, 200\u00b5L, and 50\u00b5L with a 30-second wait). Finish by adding 12\u00b5L of reagent, mixing 10 times at 20\u00b5L, incubating for 4 minutes, re-engaging magnets for 3 minutes, and transferring the final 12\u00b5L to your destination plate.",
